Class MultiFileServerPlace

public abstract class MultiFileServerPlace extends PickUpPlace implements IMultiFileServerPlace
A hybrid of the MultiFileServerPlace and the FilePickupPlace. Knows how to sprout agents using the MoveSpool

    • shouldProcess

      public boolean shouldProcess(IBaseDataObject d)
      Validate that we should process this data. Will reject null data or empty objects. Generally, all MultiFileServerPlaces should invoke this method before executing ServiceProviderPlace.process(IBaseDataObject) or ServiceProviderPlace.processHeavyDuty(IBaseDataObject). Override if your Place wants to do more validation before bothering to process a payload.
      Parameters:
      d - payload to validate
      Returns:
      true if d is not null and not empty
